line_1: And frankly leave us Human Elves,
line_2: To cut and shuffle for our selves:

line_1: But, spite of all the criticising elves,
line_2: Those who would make us feel, must feel themselves.

line_1: I wou'd have fetch'd some for th' unruly Elves;
line_2: But 'tis the Mob's delight to help Themselves:

line_1: But why repine we, that these Puny Elves
line_2: Shoot into Giants? — We may thank ourselves.

line_1: These Britons took for fairy Elves;
line_2: These tuneful Pope calls Nomes and Sylphs;
Or scorn and hate pursue yourselves.

line_1: Was one of those most happy Elves,
line_2: That dote upon their charming Selves:
Not kind, so much as to themselves,

line_1: That no such vile and upstart elves,
line_2: Should have more knowledge than themselves,

line_1: Nor roving Dæmons own, nor wandring Elves.
line_2: Men led by Sense, and partial to themselves,

line_1: A nest of linnets, a few happy elves,
line_2: Run home to see if yet they pick themselves,

line_1: When they chop logic, silly elves,
line_2: They're apt to hack and hew themselves.
